# CLAUDE.md — Job Hunt Workspace

> Generated by `job-hunt-toolkit:init-workspace`. The authoritative rules live in the plugin at `~/.claude/my-marketplace/plugins/job-hunt-toolkit/CLAUDE.md` and `references/`. This file is a local snapshot; regenerate it by re-running `init-workspace` whenever the plugin updates.

## Hard rules

- **HTML is source. PDF is export.** Edit HTML. Regenerate PDF via `/job-hunt-toolkit:export-pdf`. Never hand-edit PDFs.
- **Master is sacred.** `{{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_{{ROLE}}_CV.html` / `.pdf` at the workspace root are canonical. Tailored variants always live in `<company>/`.
- **File naming is strict.** See `NAMING.md`. Summary: underscores only, ASCII only, no spaces, no pipes, NO company name in filename.
- **Company folder naming.** lowercase with underscores (`acme_robotics/`, never `Acme Robotics/` or `acme-robotics/`).
- **Atomic commits.** HTML + PDF together, always. Never one without the other.
- **Metadata scrubbing is mandatory** before any PDF is sent. `/job-hunt-toolkit:prepare-to-send` enforces this.
- **Never fabricate experience** during tailoring. Only reframe / reorder / emphasize what's in the master CV.
- **Never commit secrets.** Salary details, recruiter private contacts, IDs — keep out of git unless user explicitly confirms.

## Workflow routing

| User intent | Skill to invoke |
|---|---|
| "start a new application" | `/job-hunt-toolkit:new-application` |
| "tailor the CV for this JD" | `resume-tailoring` skill |
| "regenerate the PDF" | `/job-hunt-toolkit:export-pdf` |
| "ready to send", "final check" | `/job-hunt-toolkit:prepare-to-send` |
| "scrub PDF metadata" | `scrub-pdf-metadata` skill |

## Per-company folder contents

Required:
- `company.md` — company snapshot with YAML frontmatter (status, applied date, recruiter, comp band)
- `job_description.*` — raw JD
- `{{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_<Role>_CV.html` — tailored source
- `{{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_<Role>_CV.pdf` — tailored export (what HR receives). **Do NOT embed the company name in the filename.**

Optional:
- `cover_letter.html` + `.pdf`
- `interview_notes.md`
- `questions_to_ask.md`
- `followups.md`

## Gotchas

- PDFs don't diff well in git. Rely on HTML diffs for real version history.
- Stripping PDF metadata with `exiftool -all=` also removes the author — re-set it after stripping.
- Chromium `--print-to-pdf` writes to CWD unless given an absolute path.
- Some HTML templates leak the source file path into headers/footers via `@page`. Scan PDFs for path-like strings during pre-send.
